00:28.094 --> 00:30.892
## [ Chorus Singing]

00:35.168 --> 00:37.136
Snacks for the gun club.

00:37.237 --> 00:40.695
I'll be backwith the drinks so you can
all get locked and loaded.

00:40.807 --> 00:43.002
[ All Laughing ]

00:43.109 --> 00:44.736
Funny.

00:44.844 --> 00:48.473
- Did you save me a cookie?
- You bet I did. Last one.

00:48.581 --> 00:50.742
Oh, cookie, you look so good.

00:50.850 --> 00:53.842
Shh, shh! Don't speak.
I'll go get some milk foryour bath.

00:53.953 --> 00:56.114
I can't believeyou're
feeding those extremists...

00:56.222 --> 00:58.554
from the National Gun Association-
They're monsters!

00:58.658 --> 01:00.956
Oh, sweetheart,
don't be so dramatic.

01:01.061 --> 01:03.222
Besides, aren'tyou having fun
cooking with Mommy?

01:03.329 --> 01:06.560
I'm not cooking with Mommy.
Dad handcuffed me to the oven!

01:06.666 --> 01:09.794
Well, ifit weren't for
handcuffs and your father...

01:09.903 --> 01:13.066
you wouldn't even
be here, young lady.

01:13.173 --> 01:15.368
What the-
Hey, that was my cookie!

01:15.475 --> 01:17.443
You snooze, you lose.

01:17.544 --> 01:21.139
You snooze, you lose, huh?

01:21.247 --> 01:23.738
Hmm. Okay. Eat up.

01:23.850 --> 01:26.375
Eat... up.

01:26.486 --> 01:30.217
Before we adjourn, let's recite
the N.G.A. oath. Hold hands.

01:30.323 --> 01:33.292
[ All Grumbling ] Come on.
It's not gay. There's guns in the room.

01:33.393 --> 01:36.055
[ Together] We pledge to uphold
the Second Amendment...

01:36.162 --> 01:39.188
and use guns responsibly
and in service to our fellow man.

01:39.299 --> 01:41.096
- [Glass Shatters ]
- [CarAlarm Wailing]

01:41.201 --> 01:44.193
Hey, somebody stop that guy!
He broke into my car and he stole my CDs!

01:44.304 --> 01:46.602
[ Together]
We pledge to act with swiftness...

01:46.706 --> 01:49.072
our ears always open
to the cries ofthose in need.

01:49.175 --> 01:51.143
[Man ]
Help! Help!

01:51.244 --> 01:54.975
[ Together] We promise to be evervigilant,
protecting our community from harm.

01:55.081 --> 01:58.539
[ Man ] And now, Action 3 News
brings you a breaking story...

01:58.651 --> 02:01.142
with anchor partners
Greg Corbin and Terry Bates.

02:01.254 --> 02:03.222
- Good evening.
- Our top story-

02:03.323 --> 02:06.656
A carwas broken into on Cherry Street
this afternoon- my car.

02:06.759 --> 02:08.954
The suspect was 6 foot 2
and a bastard!

02:09.062 --> 02:11.292
- Terry.
- No, I work hard for my things!

02:11.397 --> 02:14.127
Drinkyour tea.
You wanna cut to commercial?

02:14.234 --> 02:16.293
- Mm-hmm.
- Let's cut to commercial.

02:16.402 --> 02:18.427
Right in our
own neighborhood.

02:18.538 --> 02:22.497
Well, it's clear the time has come for me
to showyou wherewe hide our guns.

02:22.609 --> 02:24.304
GLOCK, 1 7 shots.

02:24.410 --> 02:26.708
Pen-gun,
mightierthan the sword.

02:26.813 --> 02:29.338
Sword-gun,
mightierthan the pen-gun.

02:29.449 --> 02:34.079
AR-1 5, MK5, MAC-1 0, paprika.

02:34.187 --> 02:36.587
That's weird.
I use that pantry a lot.

02:36.689 --> 02:38.554
And the paprika not enough.

02:38.658 --> 02:42.458
I can't believe this house
is teeming with guns. Guns kill.

02:42.562 --> 02:44.860
Oh, guns kill. Is that right?

02:44.964 --> 02:48.161
Well, let's see about that.
Okay, gun, kill.

02:48.268 --> 02:50.862
Go ahead. Kill someone.
Don't be shy.

02:50.970 --> 02:54.167
See? Guns don't kill people.
People kill people.

02:54.274 --> 02:56.674
Gun defend people against
people with smaller guns.

02:56.776 --> 02:58.539
- You're such a fascist.
- Peace pusher!

02:58.645 --> 03:00.044
- Murderer!
- Hermaphrodite!

03:00.146 --> 03:02.580
- Stan!
- I'm swingin' wild, Francine!

03:02.682 --> 03:05.776
Damn it! I'm tired ofyou always
being at each other's throats.

03:05.885 --> 03:07.876
You used to be best friends.

03:07.987 --> 03:10.478
Both ofyou,
in the living room now!

03:10.590 --> 03:12.956
This is howyou two
used to be.

03:13.059 --> 03:14.822
Can I fly it?

03:14.928 --> 03:17.761
Only ifyou promise
you won't fly away.

03:17.864 --> 03:20.298
- [ Giggles ]
- Oop.

03:20.400 --> 03:23.301
[Hayley Giggling]

03:23.403 --> 03:26.566
## [ Singing Together]

03:29.008 --> 03:32.705
- Hey, this is our spot! Push on!
- Are you deaf? Push on!

03:32.812 --> 03:36.304
## [ Singing Resumes ]

03:36.416 --> 03:39.078
Now, you promiseyou're just gonna
watch it once and then erase it?

03:39.185 --> 03:42.484
Yes. I just wanna
see what we look like.

03:45.825 --> 03:49.886
The point is, there was a time when
you two weren't always fighting.

03:49.996 --> 03:52.362
That was before I knew Dad
was a gun-toting maniac.

03:52.465 --> 03:54.228
- Beatnik!
- Warmonger!

03:54.334 --> 03:56.859
- Chupacabra!
- I'm the Mexican bigfoot?

03:56.970 --> 03:58.938
- You heard her. She admitted it.
- Enough!

03:59.038 --> 04:02.599
Now, tomorrowyou two are going to spend
the day together and reconnect...

04:02.709 --> 04:04.677
or I am gonna lose it!

04:05.979 --> 04:10.006
So help me, God,
I will cutyour pretty faces.

04:10.116 --> 04:13.017
- So, uh, tomorrow?
- Yeah, yeah. Tomorrow.

04:13.119 --> 04:17.452
Ach, that's the worst thing to happen to wine
since the movie Sideways.

04:17.557 --> 04:20.185
That's right, America.
Come get me.

04:20.293 --> 04:23.729
That sucks. Whywasn't I in any
ofthose old familyvideos?

04:25.465 --> 04:28.434
Well, that's 'cause all the footage
was taken beforeyou were adopted.

04:28.534 --> 04:30.729
What? What areyou talkin' about?
I'm not adopted.

04:30.837 --> 04:32.805
No, no. Of course not.
That'd be silly.

04:32.905 --> 04:36.466
You lookjust likeyour dad.
Good night.

04:36.576 --> 04:41.275
I'm gonna makeyou cry
and dip my cookie in yourtears.

04:42.882 --> 04:46.511
This is stupid.Just drop me off
and pick me up in a few hours.

04:46.619 --> 04:48.587
And risk getting
my prettyface cut?

04:48.688 --> 04:50.656
No, thanks.

04:50.757 --> 04:53.055
Well, can you at least
tell me where we're going?

04:53.159 --> 04:55.559
Remember that amusement park
we went to when you were a kid?

04:55.662 --> 04:59.189
- You're taking me to Sugar Mountain?
- You betcha, baby girl.

04:59.299 --> 05:02.666
That was the last place we went together
before I started to hateyou.

05:02.769 --> 05:04.236
Ditto.

05:06.939 --> 05:10.272
First we'll take the Rainbow Gondola
to Smile Hollow.

05:10.376 --> 05:13.072
Then we'll eat some pixie doughnuts.
Then we'll-What the-

05:13.179 --> 05:16.808
[Hayley]
N.G.A. Land? A gun park?

05:16.916 --> 05:18.884
Yeah, Sugar Mountain
closed down years ago.

05:18.985 --> 05:20.953
This is basically
the same thing...

05:21.054 --> 05:23.284
except instead of riding a choo-choo
through Fairy Book Land...

05:23.389 --> 05:25.357
you ride a bullet
through a mugger's chest.

05:25.458 --> 05:27.358
##[Carnival Organ ]

05:29.095 --> 05:31.825
[ Cheering ]

05:31.931 --> 05:36.197
You come out the exit wound!
Whee!

05:39.972 --> 05:42.406
## [ Carnival Organ ]

05:42.508 --> 05:44.499
Oh, this place is awful!

05:44.610 --> 05:47.909
Bumper Cartridges?
The Splatterhorn?

05:48.014 --> 05:50.005
Hey, at least they kept
the petting zoo.

05:51.117 --> 05:52.948
- [ Gunshot ]
- [ Gasps ]

05:53.052 --> 05:55.020
It's Ted Nugent's
Kill 'N Grill.

05:55.121 --> 05:57.089
It's his flagship eat-what-you-shoot
restaurant.

05:57.190 --> 05:59.954
## [Electric Guitar]

06:00.059 --> 06:02.027
I don't wanna
kill the rabbit.

06:02.128 --> 06:05.222
Well, you've got to kill something.
We're not stopping on the way home.

06:05.331 --> 06:08.391
Dad, this place is evil.
They're trying to push guns on kids.

06:08.501 --> 06:10.469
No, they're not.
That's absurd.

06:10.570 --> 06:15.974
[Man On P.A.] Boys andgirls, putyour
tinyhands togetherforBobbythe Bullet!

06:16.075 --> 06:19.340
[ Children Cheering ]

06:19.445 --> 06:22.437
[Man On P.A. ]
Uh-oh, kids. Who's that in the crowd?

06:22.548 --> 06:25.016
- It's A. C.L. Lou!
- Shh!

06:25.118 --> 06:26.949
[ Together ]
Boo!

06:27.053 --> 06:28.748
What do we do, kids?

06:28.855 --> 06:31.847
[ Together ]
Shoot first. Ask questions later.

06:31.958 --> 06:35.519
[ All Cheering ]

06:35.628 --> 06:38.358
[ Groaning ]

06:38.464 --> 06:40.625
You got me.

06:40.733 --> 06:42.997
Yeah!

06:45.037 --> 06:48.006
Hey, kids, listen to this.

06:48.107 --> 06:51.406
## [ Singing ]

07:06.125 --> 07:07.615
Everybody!

07:07.727 --> 07:09.695
- [ Children Cheering ]
- ##[Continues Singing]

07:09.796 --> 07:11.696
What's the meaning
of all this?

07:11.798 --> 07:14.289
Oh, God,
the N.G.A. directors.

07:14.400 --> 07:16.391
Mr. Simms, Mr. Hobart.

07:16.502 --> 07:18.470
Smith, is that
your daughter?

07:20.406 --> 07:21.873
Uh, yes, but don't worry.

07:21.974 --> 07:24.306
I'll just put a silencer on her.
Yeah, clever.

07:24.410 --> 07:26.401
Guards!

07:26.512 --> 07:30.243
Get away from me! This is a peaceful protest!
[ Grunts ]

07:34.387 --> 07:36.355
That'll come right out.

07:36.456 --> 07:38.890
Thereyou go.
This is working.

07:41.427 --> 07:44.624
You can't kick me out ofthe N.G.A.
I'm a lifetime member!

07:44.730 --> 07:47.164
- [Gunshot]
- Oh, my God!

07:47.266 --> 07:49.734
Total déjà vu right now.
This is so weird.

07:49.836 --> 07:51.804
You were right there,
just like this...

07:51.904 --> 07:54.270
and then I was overcome
with crushing disappointment.

07:54.373 --> 07:57.342
Oh, man, my card.
Oh, ho!

08:00.947 --> 08:04.781
- [ Groans ]
- I asked Mom ifl was adopted, and she said no.

08:04.884 --> 08:07.284
Well, what'd you think she was gonna say?
She's in too deep.

08:07.386 --> 08:09.354
But, hey, don't take
myword for it.

08:10.590 --> 08:13.286
I'm not in this one either.
How can this be?

08:19.165 --> 08:21.759
Look at little "Stevsie" sleep.

08:21.868 --> 08:24.302
You snooze, you lose.

08:24.403 --> 08:30.069
[ Laughing ]

08:31.644 --> 08:35.273
This must be
very painful foryou.

08:35.381 --> 08:39.578
Come on, Hayley. The N.G.A. won't reinstate
my membership unless you apologize.

08:39.684 --> 08:43.143
- Yeah, right. When pigs fly.
- Aha!

08:43.256 --> 08:45.315
- [ Rings ]
- Lab.

08:45.424 --> 08:47.119
How we doin', guys?
Did it work?

08:47.226 --> 08:49.786
[Squealing]

08:49.896 --> 08:53.593
Uh, we gotta call you back.

08:53.699 --> 08:57.601
Look, the N.G.A. is the only thing in my life
that means anything to me.

08:57.703 --> 08:59.933
- Ahem!
- What, areyou getting sick?

09:00.039 --> 09:02.132
Don't come near me.
I can't afford to get sick.

09:02.241 --> 09:05.039
So, now thatyou know
they're notyour real parents...

09:05.144 --> 09:07.374
areyou gonna call them
Stan and Francine?

09:07.480 --> 09:09.448
No, I'm gonna call them
Mom and Dad.

09:09.549 --> 09:11.517
I'm still their son.

09:11.617 --> 09:13.585
Oh, Stan, calm down.

09:13.686 --> 09:16.211
As far as I'm concerned,
we only have one child!

09:16.322 --> 09:18.916
It's like someone left the other one
on our doorstep.

09:19.025 --> 09:23.587
[ Gasps, Sobbing ]

09:23.696 --> 09:27.188
Oh, I just love it when crap
lines up like that.

09:30.603 --> 09:33.595
Mom? Dad?

09:33.706 --> 09:36.937
[Francine ]
Just take whatyou want andgo!

09:39.211 --> 09:40.610
[ Gasps ]

09:40.713 --> 09:42.544
Hayley, quick! Get the gun
in the china cabinet!

09:43.649 --> 09:45.617
[ Grunting]

09:45.718 --> 09:47.777
[ Gunshot]

09:49.155 --> 09:51.123
I- I shot him.

09:51.223 --> 09:55.819
Murderer!Just kidding. You saved
the family, kiddo. Pizza? Let's order pizza.

09:55.928 --> 09:59.796
[ Clattering]

09:59.899 --> 10:03.960
- [ Sobbing ]
- How's mylittle executionerholding up?

10:04.070 --> 10:07.528
All my life, I've said guns were bad.
I'm such a hypocrite.

10:07.640 --> 10:09.608
Honey,
he was robbing us...

10:09.709 --> 10:12.473
- and he was gonna force himself on me.
- He said that?

10:12.578 --> 10:15.411
Well, no, but I assume.

10:15.514 --> 10:18.278
What? You think
I'm not attractive enough?

10:18.384 --> 10:21.319
That what? That he'd just skip me
and go straight toyou?

10:21.420 --> 10:23.388
Well, aren'twe conceited.

10:23.489 --> 10:25.923
Mom, I killed someone.

10:26.025 --> 10:28.016
Sweetheart,
you had no choice.

10:28.127 --> 10:30.095
You saved the family.

10:30.196 --> 10:32.721
Yeah, I did, huh?
And with a gun.

10:32.832 --> 10:34.800
I guess I owe the N.G.A.
that apology.

10:34.900 --> 10:36.868
[Laughter]

10:36.969 --> 10:38.834
What the hell?

10:38.938 --> 10:42.999
That's the burglar!
Dad staged the whole thing!

10:43.109 --> 10:47.011
Yeah, I get it, Hayley.
I'm "unrapable," not stupid.

10:47.113 --> 10:49.343
- You lunatic!
- [ Gasps ]

10:49.448 --> 10:53.475
You tricked us just soyou could get
an apology out of Hayley?

10:53.586 --> 10:56.953
Is your gun club that important toyou?
And you!

10:57.790 --> 11:00.759
You missed out, pal.

11:00.860 --> 11:03.488
Dad! I thought
I killed someone.

11:03.596 --> 11:05.826
Aha! You thought
you killed someone.

11:05.931 --> 11:07.899
Before, you said guns kill,
not people.

11:08.000 --> 11:10.525
- [ Laughs ] I win!
- Someone could have been hurt.

11:10.636 --> 11:12.968
- Relax. They're just blanks.
- Blanks?

11:13.072 --> 11:16.735
Oh, hi, I'm Stan Smith.
I think it's cool to trick my daughter.

11:16.842 --> 11:19.242
Who cares if
it scars her for life?

11:19.345 --> 11:22.041
I guess they
weren't all blanks.

11:23.282 --> 11:26.183
Dad!
Help him!

11:26.285 --> 11:28.981
Call a real ambulance!

11:33.225 --> 11:36.126
The, uh, bullet is lodged
in your spine...

11:36.228 --> 11:38.389
and, I'm afraid,
forthe rest ofyour life...

11:38.497 --> 11:40.465
you'll be
a quadriplegic.

11:40.566 --> 11:44.127
Well, that sounds fancy. Come on, people.
Souplantation on Daddy!

11:50.976 --> 11:52.944
Daddy, I madeyou
some soup.

11:53.045 --> 11:55.275
Let it cool,
'cause it's much, much too hot.

11:55.381 --> 11:57.611
- [ Screams ]
- Oh, my God!

11:57.717 --> 12:00.311
[ Laughs ]
I got you! I can't feel a thing.

12:00.419 --> 12:02.387
Hayley, why don't you
get some sleep?

12:02.488 --> 12:04.922
You haven't left your father's
side in three days.

12:05.024 --> 12:06.719
This was my fault.

12:06.826 --> 12:09.488
Hey, don't worry about me.
I'm still your same old dad.

12:09.595 --> 12:11.563
What's that sound?

12:11.664 --> 12:13.632
Oh, I'm peeing.
Fantastic!

12:15.067 --> 12:17.968
Hey, I found
your real parents online.

12:18.070 --> 12:21.631
Stan and Francine didn't adoptyou.
They kidnapped you.

12:21.741 --> 12:25.370
- What?
- Yep, they nabbed you when you were three...

12:25.478 --> 12:27.571
- from a boat show.
- [ Gasps ]

12:27.680 --> 12:29.841
That explains why
I've always wanted a boat.

12:29.949 --> 12:32.247
Well, there you go, Tom.

12:32.351 --> 12:34.546
That's your real name.
Tom Madsen.

12:34.653 --> 12:36.985
Wow. Tom Madsen.

12:37.089 --> 12:40.923
You know, the name Smith never felt right.
It's not a seafaring name.

12:41.026 --> 12:44.826
No, but Madsen- that's Norwegian.
So, Tom...

12:44.930 --> 12:47.558
- how'd you like to meetyour real parents?
- [ Gasps ]

12:49.769 --> 12:51.737
Thanks for
pimpin' my ride, Hayley.

12:52.972 --> 12:56.237
[ Blowing, Inhales ]

12:59.378 --> 13:02.176
Whoo! A little light-headed.
Did my streamers catch wind?

13:02.281 --> 13:06.843
Um, yeah. Look, Dad, now that
you can't work at the C.I.A....

13:06.952 --> 13:09.614
haveyou given any thought to what
you want to do with your life?

13:09.722 --> 13:13.954
I sure have. I wanna make a difference.
I wanna be an activist.

13:14.059 --> 13:17.790
Really?
Oh, that's great, Dad!

13:17.897 --> 13:21.526
Thanks, honey. Come on over here
and giveyour dad a hug.

13:24.937 --> 13:28.771
Now let's go and have a little talk
with those boys at the N.G.A.

13:28.874 --> 13:30.842
- Right on!
- Hey, Son.

13:30.943 --> 13:33.707
Don't "Son" me,
baby snatcher.

13:33.813 --> 13:35.781
Somethin'on
yourmind, champ?

13:35.881 --> 13:37.849
Steve, what are you doing?

13:37.950 --> 13:41.442
Something we've both
wanted to do foryears, "Sis."

13:41.554 --> 13:45.991
- Mmm!
- [ Muffled Squealing ]

13:47.426 --> 13:49.394
Oh, my God!

13:49.495 --> 13:52.589
Everything that happens from this point on
is just gravy.

13:55.134 --> 13:57.193
My dad was paralyzed
in a gun accident...

13:57.303 --> 13:59.271
and he has something
to say about it.

13:59.371 --> 14:01.669
- Tell 'em, Dad.
- I will, Hayley.

14:01.774 --> 14:05.403
Gentlemen, my body is lifeless,
but my brain still works.

14:05.511 --> 14:08.742
And it's telling me
to tell my mouth to tell you...

14:08.848 --> 14:11.612
that I want to be a progun
spokesman for the N.G.A.

14:11.717 --> 14:12.484
What?

14:12.484 --> 14:13.416
What?

14:13.519 --> 14:15.146
Who better than me?

14:15.254 --> 14:18.417
What's left of my spine tells the whole story.
Guns work.

14:18.524 --> 14:20.492
Butyou were paralyzed by a gun!

14:20.593 --> 14:22.561
No, I was paralyzed byyou.

14:22.661 --> 14:24.629
Look, I'm not gonna
point fingers here.

14:24.730 --> 14:26.925
Because I can't.
Because ofyou.

14:27.032 --> 14:29.125
We already have a spokesman.

14:29.235 --> 14:31.635
Actually, the kids never really did
embraceyou, Bobby.

14:31.737 --> 14:33.830
Butyou know what
the kids did respond to?

14:33.939 --> 14:36.271
- His daughter's music.
- [ All ] Mm-hmm.

14:36.375 --> 14:41.369
How about it, Smith? This Saturday
is the No Child Left Unarmed Jamboree.

14:41.480 --> 14:44.005
Ifyou and your daughter perform,
you're our new spokesman.

14:44.116 --> 14:46.107
- Yes!
- No!

14:46.218 --> 14:50.416
Dad, I'd do anything foryou,
but this goes against everything I stand for.

14:50.522 --> 14:52.581
Mmm, "stand."

14:52.691 --> 14:55.683
That's okay.
I respect howyou feel.

14:55.794 --> 14:58.354
Mmm, "feel."

14:58.464 --> 15:00.432
Okay, I'll do it.

15:00.532 --> 15:02.898
Really? Yes!
Victory lap!

15:07.840 --> 15:09.967
Bobby, you're fired.
Turn in the costume.

15:10.075 --> 15:12.407
Never!

15:17.182 --> 15:20.083
Whywould I wear a sailor suit
to meet my real parents?

15:20.185 --> 15:22.380
You were kidnapped
at a boat show.

15:22.488 --> 15:24.456
Your parents have a boat.
They're rich.

15:24.556 --> 15:27.286
- You want them to recognizeyou or not?
- You're right. You're right.

15:27.393 --> 15:29.418
Don't forget
this curly blond wig.

15:29.528 --> 15:32.429
- Whywould I wear a wig?
- You're Norwegian.

15:32.531 --> 15:35.022
Right, right.

15:38.771 --> 15:42.036
Hmm, I'm stuck on these lyrics.
What rhymes with ammo?

15:42.141 --> 15:45.770
Empty shell ofa girl
who's completely sold out hervalues?

15:45.878 --> 15:48.403
No, I'm pretty sure
it should end with an "O."

15:48.514 --> 15:52.109
- [ Sighs ] "Blammo"?
- Blammo. Good, good, good.

15:52.217 --> 15:56.677
Look atyou two. Who would have thought
guns would bring you so close together?

15:56.789 --> 16:00.350
I know. If onlywe could get
some guns to the Middle East.

16:04.730 --> 16:07.392
- [ Sighs ]
- [Doorbell Rings ]

16:07.499 --> 16:11.458
Mr. Madsen?
I'm Tom, your son.

16:11.570 --> 16:14.505
Oh, my God.
Tommy!

16:14.606 --> 16:17.598
Is it reallyyou?
Jane, come quick!

16:17.710 --> 16:21.407
- Mama?
- Thomas! You are alive!

16:21.513 --> 16:24.971
All theseyears,
we never gave up hope.

16:27.019 --> 16:30.921
Gotcha! Those aren'tyour parents!
That's for taking my cookie!

16:31.023 --> 16:34.049
- What?
- Remember? "You snooze, you lose"?

16:34.159 --> 16:36.525
You-You put me
through all this...

16:36.628 --> 16:39.620
j-just because
I ate your cookie?

16:39.732 --> 16:42.826
Dude, that is awesome!

16:42.935 --> 16:44.903
You so got me!

16:45.004 --> 16:48.963
Thanks. Thanks. There were a couple times
when I didn't thinkyou were buying it.

16:49.074 --> 16:51.668
Hey, I'm in a sailor suit.
[ Laughs ]

16:51.777 --> 16:53.677
Man, I should have known.
These people aren't rich.

16:53.779 --> 16:55.747
Look at their house.
It's a box.

16:55.848 --> 16:58.009
Oh, oh!
Picture. Picture.

17:01.153 --> 17:03.621
- ##[Rock Song Ending]
- [ Children Cheering]

17:03.722 --> 17:05.622
[ Cheering Continues ]

17:05.723 --> 17:08.386
Thankyou.
That was "Suzy Shot a Unicorn."

17:10.095 --> 17:13.087
- Look, kids, it's snowing!
- [ Children Cheering]

17:13.198 --> 17:16.223
- Hey, Santa!
- ## [Rock]

17:16.335 --> 17:19.031
## [ Singing ]

17:26.744 --> 17:29.646
## [ Together]

17:50.035 --> 17:53.232
## [ Together]

17:59.478 --> 18:02.003
## [ Ends ]

18:02.114 --> 18:04.981
[ All Cheering ]

18:06.919 --> 18:08.887
Listen to that, honey.

18:08.987 --> 18:11.512
The most beautiful sound
in the world- kids screaming.

18:11.623 --> 18:13.648
I'm glad you're happy, Dad.

18:13.759 --> 18:16.922
Stan, I don't think Hayley's
having as much fun as you are.

18:17.029 --> 18:19.862
- What areyou talkin' about?
- [ Vomiting ]

18:19.965 --> 18:22.798
Don'tyou see, Stan?
She's miserable.

18:22.901 --> 18:24.869
She's given up everything
she believes in...

18:24.970 --> 18:27.666
because she feels
awful about hurting you.

18:27.773 --> 18:29.900
I hateyou.
You make me sick.

18:31.176 --> 18:33.144
- I'm not seein' it.
- Smith!

18:33.245 --> 18:35.736
- The crowd demands an encore.
- Come on, Hayley. You ready?

18:35.848 --> 18:39.648
- Sure, Dad.
- [ Children Cheering]

18:39.751 --> 18:41.412
You suck!

18:41.520 --> 18:44.318
All right, let's do
"Ammo Blammo."

18:54.066 --> 18:56.034
What's wrong?
You missed your cue.

18:56.135 --> 19:00.094
What's wrong? [ Sighs ]
I was wrong. I can't makeyou do this.

19:00.205 --> 19:02.935
- [ All Gasping, Murmuring ]
- What areyou talking about?

19:03.041 --> 19:06.568
I knowyou're only doing this because
you blameyourselffor hurting me.

19:06.678 --> 19:08.703
Butyou would never hurt me.

19:08.814 --> 19:13.251
And ifyou didn't hurt me,
that only leaves the gun.

19:13.352 --> 19:16.947
Which means-
Which means guns are bad.

19:17.055 --> 19:19.990
This is a song
my daughterwrote.

19:20.092 --> 19:24.028
## [ Singing ]

19:29.401 --> 19:31.369
## [Together]

19:37.409 --> 19:40.708
Wow! Ifthe hot girl doesn't like guns,
I guess I don't either.

19:40.812 --> 19:42.780
Uh-oh, we're losin' 'em.

19:42.881 --> 19:45.076
This is my chance
to get myjob back.

19:45.184 --> 19:47.584
##[HayleySinging]

19:49.555 --> 19:50.886
## [ Fades ]

19:54.426 --> 19:56.587
[ Inhales ]

20:01.934 --> 20:04.198
[CrowdScreaming]

20:05.337 --> 20:07.897
Dad! Oh, my God!
He's been shot!

20:08.006 --> 20:11.442
Hayley, tell Roger...

20:11.543 --> 20:13.511
he's annoying.

20:16.114 --> 20:18.082
Well, this time
whenyou were shot-

20:19.685 --> 20:23.621
Whoop! That's my X-ray-size
vacation slide. Here we go.

20:23.722 --> 20:27.556
See? The second bullet passed through
your neck and pushed the first bullet out.

20:27.659 --> 20:29.627
You should be completely
ambulatory again.

20:29.728 --> 20:32.595
What good is that
to a man who has to spend...

20:32.698 --> 20:35.258
the rest ofhis life in a chair?

20:35.367 --> 20:38.564
[ Screams ]
Doc, your fork has magical powers!

20:38.670 --> 20:41.764
- It's the bullet that saved you.
- This is great!

20:41.873 --> 20:44.808
We've gotta go back on tour
and spread the word. Guns are good!

20:44.910 --> 20:47.674
- What?
- Without guns, I'd still be in a wheelchair.

20:47.779 --> 20:49.747
Guns heal the sick.

20:49.848 --> 20:51.816
[ Sighs ]

20:51.917 --> 20:54.647
Did somebody order
40 c.c.'s of deliciousness?

20:54.753 --> 20:56.721
We found goodies
in the lobby.

20:56.822 --> 20:59.882
Wiffle Wicks, Bittles, Grape Gum-
Hey, you're in my seat.

20:59.992 --> 21:03.018
Sorry. Early bird
gets the worm.

21:03.128 --> 21:06.757
Early bird gets the worm, huh?

21:06.865 --> 21:09.356
Yeah, enjoy the seat.

21:09.468 --> 21:12.596
Enjoy... the seat.

21:45.170 --> 21:47.070
Have a great night.

